        "cmip6.atmos.radiation.name": {
            "values": [
                "Atmospheric radiation scheme dealing with gas molecules and aerosol and cloud particles"
            ]
        }, 
        "cmip6.atmos.radiation.overview": {
            "values": [
                "The scheme conducts 1D radiation transfer computation with several bands divided in   longwave (LW, infrared) and shortwave (SW, solar) spectral region. Major absorption gases are considered in both region and absorption due to green-house gases is also taken into account in the LW region. Absorption and emission process are considered in the LW region and absorption and scattering process are considered in the SW region. Optical properties of cloud droplets and ice crystals are parameterized with cloud effective sizes. Aerosol direct effect is computed depending on aerosol species and the indirect effect to cloud droplets is simply taken into account by using different cloud effective radii over the ocean and the land. In the atmospheric model, homogeneous cloud is assumed in each layer and the vertical cloud overlap assumption is applied in the radiative transfer computation."
            ]
        }, 
